ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this class. If your studies are at all relevant to computational science, I found that this class taught me the most useful and interesting information.
Yes I would recommend it. It requires a fair amount of work but the effort you put in will be absolutely worth it.
I think I would recommend this course to another student in CS department, but maybe not to students in other fields.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learned how to become a better programmer, by learning crucial techniques for debugging, and learned new "hacks" to determine if previous programs I had written were working and how to make them better.
It helps me understand the mining algos more deep and more mathematically.
